1
00:01:25,710 --> 00:01:34,930
[LIVE UP TO YOUR YOUTH]

2
00:01:35,280 --> 00:01:37,920
[Episode 27]

3
00:01:38,220 --> 00:01:41,710
[Wenzhou Bus Station]

4
00:01:41,710 --> 00:01:44,670
[Dangerous items
strictly prohibited on board.]

5
00:01:45,680 --> 00:01:47,479
What are you looking around for?

6
00:01:47,700 --> 00:01:48,810
Nothing.

7
00:01:49,400 --> 00:01:50,340
Looking for love, huh?

8
00:01:50,340 --> 00:01:51,150
No!

9
00:01:52,640 --> 00:01:53,170
Have one.

10
00:01:53,320 --> 00:01:53,979
No, thanks.

11
00:01:54,110 --> 00:01:55,870
Let's go. Let's eat it on the bus.

12
00:01:55,870 --> 00:01:56,400
Let's go.

13
00:01:57,370 --> 00:01:57,900
Careful.

14
00:02:02,200 --> 00:02:03,930
How are things with Chief Engineer Pan?

15
00:02:03,930 --> 00:02:05,060
Chief Engineer Pan?

16
00:02:06,000 --> 00:02:06,760
I have to

17
00:02:06,760 --> 00:02:08,020
get him on board no matter what!

18
00:02:08,020 --> 00:02:08,750
At least I can

19
00:02:08,759 --> 00:02:10,240
finally get even with Director Wang.

20
00:02:10,240 --> 00:02:10,590
Okay.

21
00:02:10,750 --> 00:02:12,090
Once things are settled here,

22
00:02:12,090 --> 00:02:13,550
we need to hurry to Russia.

23
00:02:13,810 --> 00:02:14,960
The weather gets cold quickly there.

24
00:02:14,960 --> 00:02:17,760
We'll miss the season
if we don't rush production.

25
00:02:18,079 --> 00:02:19,020
Like I don't know that.

26
00:02:19,020 --> 00:02:19,710
I've been to Russia

27
00:02:19,710 --> 00:02:20,840
more times than you.

28
00:02:24,010 --> 00:02:24,670
[Wenzhou; Jinhua]

29
00:02:24,670 --> 00:02:25,680
[Wenzhou; Shaoxing]

30
00:02:30,260 --> 00:02:31,100
Xu Shengli!

31
00:02:42,300 --> 00:02:44,730
[Dangerous items
strictly prohibited on board.]

32
00:02:43,870 --> 00:02:44,800
Why are you here?

33
00:02:45,329 --> 00:02:46,070
What?

34
00:02:46,380 --> 00:02:48,110
You came to see me off in person?

35
00:02:48,680 --> 00:02:49,540
Not funny, huh?

36
00:02:50,210 --> 00:02:51,020
You guys talk.

37
00:02:52,690 --> 00:02:53,350
Wait, wait.

38
00:02:54,280 --> 00:02:54,960
It's fine. You don't have to!

39
00:02:54,960 --> 00:02:55,920
Come on, let me!

40
00:02:56,100 --> 00:02:56,560
Come on.

41
00:02:59,100 --> 00:03:00,230
Did Mr. Ye help us out

42
00:03:00,360 --> 00:03:01,660
with the factory?

43
00:03:01,800 --> 00:03:03,130
Please thank him for us.

44
00:03:03,850 --> 00:03:05,180
Good that he could help.

45
00:03:08,000 --> 00:03:09,930
My mom insisted I bring this to you.

46
00:03:09,930 --> 00:03:10,860
Eat it on the way.

47
00:03:11,660 --> 00:03:12,940
Okay. Tell your mom

48
00:03:12,970 --> 00:03:15,030
I'll come visit her again next month.

49
00:03:15,070 --> 00:03:15,800
Alright.

50
00:03:16,130 --> 00:03:17,390
No need to be so polite.

51
00:03:20,660 --> 00:03:27,610
[Dangerous items
strictly prohibited on board.]

52
00:03:23,540 --> 00:03:24,740
Be careful. Careful.

53
00:03:28,960 --> 00:03:30,520
Then take care of your mom,

54
00:03:30,550 --> 00:03:32,250
and take good care of yourself as well.

55
00:03:32,250 --> 00:03:33,100
If you fall ill,

56
00:03:33,100 --> 00:03:34,430
no one will take care of her,

57
00:03:34,430 --> 00:03:36,160
and no one will take care of you.

58
00:03:40,210 --> 00:03:41,329
All right. Go now.

59
00:03:44,060 --> 00:03:45,410
Be safe on the road.

60
00:03:49,170 --> 00:03:52,170
Don't go sticking your neck out
if something happens.

61
00:03:53,220 --> 00:03:54,750
Okay, I'll go then.

62
00:03:59,870 --> 00:04:00,370
Bye.

63
00:04:04,530 --> 00:04:05,100
Bye.

64
00:04:17,140 --> 00:04:17,579
Bye.

65
00:04:49,440 --> 00:04:50,450
If you really can't bear to leave,

66
00:04:50,450 --> 00:04:51,070
just stay.

67
00:04:51,430 --> 00:04:52,840
I can manage the business on my own.

68
00:04:52,840 --> 00:04:54,330
I'll still give you your share.

69
00:04:54,330 --> 00:04:54,870
No need!

70
00:04:56,659 --> 00:04:57,659
Let's make money!

71
00:05:11,010 --> 00:05:13,470
Ivan really has built up
quite an operation.

72
00:05:13,870 --> 00:05:14,830
No wonder people say

73
00:05:14,830 --> 00:05:15,500
that the best leather jackets

74
00:05:15,500 --> 00:05:16,890
and shoes on the market

75
00:05:16,920 --> 00:05:18,060
all use his hides.

76
00:05:20,840 --> 00:05:22,070
But we don't know

77
00:05:22,130 --> 00:05:23,130
the trade jargon in Russian.

78
00:05:23,130 --> 00:05:24,360
How are we supposed to communicate?

79
00:05:24,360 --> 00:05:25,300
It doesn't matter.

80
00:05:25,300 --> 00:05:26,630
You only need two things

81
00:05:26,660 --> 00:05:27,310
to do business in Russia:

82
00:05:27,310 --> 00:05:28,840
first, bring a calculator.

83
00:05:29,010 --> 00:05:29,640
Second,

84
00:05:29,810 --> 00:05:30,950
say "Harasho" (very good) to everyone.

85
00:05:30,950 --> 00:05:32,080
Guaranteed to work.

86
00:05:32,430 --> 00:05:33,150
That's him?

87
00:05:33,430 --> 00:05:34,960
-That should be him.
-Ivan!

88
00:05:35,150 --> 00:05:35,580
Yes.

89
00:05:36,250 --> 00:05:37,540
Harasho! Harasho!

90
00:05:37,870 --> 00:05:38,870
You're here.

91
00:05:39,990 --> 00:05:41,330
Was it cold on the way?

92
00:05:43,100 --> 00:05:44,920
Well, we came by train.

93
00:05:45,810 --> 00:05:47,630
There was heating, so it was very warm.

94
00:05:47,630 --> 00:05:48,800
Nice to meet you.

95
00:05:48,820 --> 00:05:49,510
Nice to meet you.

96
00:05:49,510 --> 00:05:50,440
Nice to meet you.

97
00:05:50,570 --> 00:05:52,570
You speak really good Chinese.

98
00:05:52,830 --> 00:05:54,430
When friends come from afar,

99
00:05:54,690 --> 00:05:56,350
you must show them sincerity.

100
00:05:57,830 --> 00:05:59,830
He even knows our Chinese proverbs.

101
00:05:59,830 --> 00:06:01,990
Well, we'd like to see the goods first.

102
00:06:02,980 --> 00:06:04,200
Take a look at the hides.

103
00:06:04,200 --> 00:06:04,690
Sure.

104
00:06:05,830 --> 00:06:06,270
Okay.

105
00:06:21,270 --> 00:06:22,560
They could've just put it there directly.

106
00:06:22,560 --> 00:06:23,820
Totally unnecessary.

107
00:06:52,159 --> 00:06:53,690
They're top-grain leather

108
00:06:53,790 --> 00:06:55,000
from Chita's ranches.

109
00:06:55,000 --> 00:06:56,940
See how firmly frozen they are.

110
00:06:59,800 --> 00:07:01,730
Evenly salted, with no hard spots.

111
00:07:01,770 --> 00:07:02,500
Pretty good.

112
00:07:02,630 --> 00:07:04,470
Very good. Harasho.

113
00:07:04,570 --> 00:07:05,700
You know your stuff.

114
00:07:06,920 --> 00:07:08,050
This batch of goods—

115
00:07:08,070 --> 00:07:10,180
small orders, $4 a piece.

116
00:07:10,870 --> 00:07:13,540
Large orders, $3 per piece.

117
00:07:13,890 --> 00:07:14,750
Three dollars?

118
00:07:15,130 --> 00:07:16,630
In cash, $2.50 a piece.

119
00:07:17,800 --> 00:07:19,950
Look at these buffalo hides.

120
00:07:21,390 --> 00:07:22,740
The quality is excellent.

121
00:07:22,740 --> 00:07:25,630
Perfect for making protective work gloves.

122
00:07:26,430 --> 00:07:28,360
He says these are buffalo hides,

123
00:07:28,400 --> 00:07:29,660
known for durability.

124
00:07:31,510 --> 00:07:32,330
But we don't have

125
00:07:32,330 --> 00:07:33,790
that much money right now.

126
00:07:34,659 --> 00:07:36,390
And the prices are pretty high.

127
00:07:37,540 --> 00:07:40,040
We need 200 pieces of this kind of hide

128
00:07:40,580 --> 00:07:41,840
and 100 buffalo hides.

129
00:07:42,970 --> 00:07:43,900
No problem.

130
00:07:44,750 --> 00:07:47,520
You've already found a factory in China?

131
00:07:47,650 --> 00:07:48,450
Yes, we have.

132
00:07:49,040 --> 00:07:50,010
I-In Wenzhou.

133
00:07:50,120 --> 00:07:51,210
It's fully equipped.

134
00:07:51,210 --> 00:07:51,960
Wenzhou.

135
00:07:53,030 --> 00:07:54,360
I know Wenzhou.

136
00:07:54,390 --> 00:07:55,320
I've been there.

137
00:07:56,500 --> 00:07:58,510
The factories there are really good.

138
00:07:58,510 --> 00:08:00,890
They specialize in leather production.

139
00:08:01,440 --> 00:08:04,650
We Russians also purchase from there.

140
00:08:06,250 --> 00:08:08,060
All I caught was "harasho."

141
00:08:08,480 --> 00:08:10,120
Um... I didn't understand.

142
00:08:10,120 --> 00:08:12,850
Could you just speak simple Chinese?

143
00:08:14,950 --> 00:08:17,210
Get the money ready and pick up the goods.

144
00:08:19,770 --> 00:08:20,130
Okay.

145
00:08:22,100 --> 00:08:22,900
No problem.

146
00:08:23,480 --> 00:08:24,540
To our friendship!

147
00:08:24,690 --> 00:08:25,220
Harasho!

148
00:08:26,180 --> 00:08:26,900
Harasho!

149
00:08:28,630 --> 00:08:29,750
Take care.

150
00:08:37,130 --> 00:08:38,820
The factory deposit is 30,000,

151
00:08:38,820 --> 00:08:40,669
and the hides alone will cost 10,000.

152
00:08:40,669 --> 00:08:41,270
We don't have

153
00:08:41,270 --> 00:08:42,730
that much money right now.

154
00:08:43,130 --> 00:08:44,770
How about we make a couple of trips

155
00:08:44,770 --> 00:08:45,940
to sell some small goods

156
00:08:45,940 --> 00:08:47,410
and raise some startup capital?

157
00:08:47,410 --> 00:08:48,480
If we do that,

158
00:08:48,500 --> 00:08:50,370
how long will it take to get the money?

159
00:08:50,370 --> 00:08:51,340
You just don't know

160
00:08:51,340 --> 00:08:52,670
what kind of person I am.

161
00:08:53,120 --> 00:08:53,720
I'm...

162
00:08:54,410 --> 00:08:55,480
Plenty of people will lend me money

163
00:08:55,480 --> 00:08:56,280
for business.

164
00:08:56,360 --> 00:08:57,080
Let's not go too far—

165
00:08:57,080 --> 00:08:58,100
take Sophia, for example.

166
00:08:58,100 --> 00:08:58,890
She'll definitely chip in.

167
00:08:58,890 --> 00:08:59,980
But we can't take money from a woman,

168
00:08:59,980 --> 00:09:00,460
right?

169
00:09:00,910 --> 00:09:02,150
Here's the plan—
I'll go back, make some calls,

170
00:09:02,150 --> 00:09:03,200
and ask some friends to lend us some.

171
00:09:03,200 --> 00:09:04,060
Piece of cake!

172
00:09:05,100 --> 00:09:05,560
Well...

173
00:09:06,080 --> 00:09:08,600
When I reach out,
support comes from everywhere!

174
00:09:08,600 --> 00:09:09,250
Okay, okay.

175
00:09:09,250 --> 00:09:10,580
Let's go. Get in the car.

176
00:09:10,820 --> 00:09:12,480
I'll drive, and you sit there.

177
00:09:17,910 --> 00:09:18,570
M-Mr. Duan,

178
00:09:19,170 --> 00:09:20,000
let me tell you.

179
00:09:20,000 --> 00:09:21,410
I, Ma Xiaojun—Lucky Ma—

180
00:09:21,440 --> 00:09:23,170
stay true to my name and myself,

181
00:09:23,240 --> 00:09:23,530
right?

182
00:09:23,530 --> 00:09:24,440
You know what kind of person I am.

183
00:09:24,440 --> 00:09:26,250
We've known each other for so long!

184
00:09:26,250 --> 00:09:26,880
Xiaojun,

185
00:09:27,320 --> 00:09:28,590
of course I know you.

186
00:09:28,740 --> 00:09:29,620
I trust you.

187
00:09:30,410 --> 00:09:31,340
But you also know

188
00:09:31,360 --> 00:09:31,860
my business hasn't been

189
00:09:31,860 --> 00:09:33,660
going well these past few years.

190
00:09:34,030 --> 00:09:35,190
So this time,

191
00:09:35,620 --> 00:09:36,750
I really can't help you.

192
00:09:36,750 --> 00:09:37,310
How about this?

193
00:09:37,310 --> 00:09:39,280
Try asking someone else,

194
00:09:39,340 --> 00:09:39,890
okay?

195
00:09:40,270 --> 00:09:41,270
Alright, then...

196
00:09:41,550 --> 00:09:41,980
Alright.

197
00:09:41,980 --> 00:09:43,530
I'll treat you to a meal when I get back.

198
00:09:43,530 --> 00:09:44,190
Hanging up.

199
00:09:44,340 --> 00:09:45,010
Okay.

200
00:09:53,510 --> 00:09:54,250
Let me guess—

201
00:09:55,200 --> 00:09:57,800
someone calling
to borrow money again, right?

202
00:09:58,520 --> 00:09:59,580
You guessed right.

203
00:10:00,750 --> 00:10:01,410
That was...

204
00:10:02,270 --> 00:10:03,170
a young friend I met

205
00:10:03,170 --> 00:10:04,440
about four or five years ago.

206
00:10:04,440 --> 00:10:05,040
Recently,

207
00:10:05,100 --> 00:10:07,390
he's been doing business
with a group of young people.

208
00:10:07,390 --> 00:10:08,130
But none of them

209
00:10:08,130 --> 00:10:09,130
have proper jobs,

210
00:10:09,220 --> 00:10:10,600
and they even live in
a basement here.

211
00:10:10,600 --> 00:10:12,130
Well, how can I lend them...

212
00:10:12,770 --> 00:10:13,770
Don't look down on

213
00:10:13,770 --> 00:10:15,370
those who live in basements.

214
00:10:15,370 --> 00:10:17,100
Who hasn't lived in one before?

215
00:10:20,890 --> 00:10:21,750
You don't know.

216
00:10:22,020 --> 00:10:22,990
This young man

217
00:10:23,020 --> 00:10:25,120
always jumps from one idea to another.

218
00:10:25,120 --> 00:10:26,200
Not long ago, he took them

219
00:10:26,200 --> 00:10:27,260
on a tour doing gigs.

220
00:10:27,260 --> 00:10:29,130
Well, that was totally unrealistic.

221
00:10:29,130 --> 00:10:29,820
Do gigs?

222
00:10:30,890 --> 00:10:31,890
What kind of gigs?

223
00:10:33,550 --> 00:10:35,130
He was with some

224
00:10:35,150 --> 00:10:37,550
childhood friend who plays the saxophone,

225
00:10:37,840 --> 00:10:39,660
and another one is a...

226
00:10:39,680 --> 00:10:40,540
screenwriter.

227
00:10:41,370 --> 00:10:42,390
He spent ages

228
00:10:42,390 --> 00:10:43,460
pitching their plan to me—

229
00:10:43,460 --> 00:10:44,750
said that in three years,

230
00:10:44,750 --> 00:10:47,660
each of them would make half a million.

231
00:10:47,980 --> 00:10:48,690
You tell me,

232
00:10:49,170 --> 00:10:51,230
does that sound remotely realistic?

233
00:10:52,150 --> 00:10:53,880
How much do they want to borrow?

234
00:11:01,680 --> 00:11:02,360
Mr. Duan.

235
00:11:07,100 --> 00:11:07,850
R-Really?

236
00:11:08,220 --> 00:11:09,780
Yes, it's true.

237
00:11:09,810 --> 00:11:10,600
Xiaojun,

238
00:11:10,790 --> 00:11:11,990
you're really lucky.

239
00:11:13,250 --> 00:11:14,690
A business partner of mine

240
00:11:14,690 --> 00:11:16,620
just transferred some money to me.

241
00:11:17,170 --> 00:11:19,030
You called me at the perfect time.

242
00:11:19,270 --> 00:11:19,800
Alright.

243
00:11:20,090 --> 00:11:21,410
Everyone runs into difficulties sometimes.

244
00:11:21,410 --> 00:11:22,340
First thing tomorrow morning

245
00:11:22,340 --> 00:11:23,800
I'll wire the money to you.

246
00:11:23,950 --> 00:11:25,320
Thank you, Mr. Duan! Thank you!

247
00:11:25,320 --> 00:11:26,000
H-How about this:

248
00:11:26,000 --> 00:11:27,250
I'll write an IOU

249
00:11:27,250 --> 00:11:27,940
and send it to you.

250
00:11:27,940 --> 00:11:29,510
Or I can have my friend in our hometown

251
00:11:29,510 --> 00:11:30,000
write an IOU

252
00:11:30,000 --> 00:11:31,100
to you!

253
00:11:31,200 --> 00:11:31,740
And for interest,

254
00:11:31,740 --> 00:11:32,940
we'll go by the bank rate,

255
00:11:32,940 --> 00:11:33,650
whatever that comes to.

256
00:11:33,650 --> 00:11:34,440
Is that okay, Mr. Duan?

257
00:11:34,440 --> 00:11:35,770
Forget about interest.

258
00:11:35,960 --> 00:11:37,470
Take the money and use it.

259
00:11:37,750 --> 00:11:39,510
Just work hard, make money,

260
00:11:39,840 --> 00:11:40,620
and pay back every last yuan

261
00:11:40,620 --> 00:11:42,050
of the 50,000.

262
00:11:42,050 --> 00:11:43,110
That'll be enough.

263
00:11:44,630 --> 00:11:45,320
Thank you, Mr. Duan.

264
00:11:45,320 --> 00:11:46,050
You're really too kind.

265
00:11:46,050 --> 00:11:46,940
Really, I don't even know

266
00:11:46,940 --> 00:11:47,620
how to thank you.

267
00:11:47,620 --> 00:11:49,290
When I get back, I'll definitely

268
00:11:49,290 --> 00:11:49,720
treat you to a meal.

269
00:11:49,720 --> 00:11:51,420
I'll thank you properly, Mr. Duan.

270
00:11:51,420 --> 00:11:52,950
Alright, don't mention it.

271
00:11:53,200 --> 00:11:53,800
Actually,

272
00:11:53,940 --> 00:11:54,730
this money

273
00:11:55,150 --> 00:11:56,440
isn't exactly

274
00:11:56,500 --> 00:11:57,370
my money.

275
00:11:58,150 --> 00:11:59,370
Alright, let's not talk about this.

276
00:11:59,370 --> 00:11:59,920
Xiaojun,

277
00:12:00,130 --> 00:12:01,530
work hard.

278
00:12:01,700 --> 00:12:03,120
When you've made it

279
00:12:03,720 --> 00:12:04,920
and come back safely,

280
00:12:05,120 --> 00:12:06,270
I'll throw you a welcome party.

281
00:12:06,270 --> 00:12:06,550
Mr. Duan,

282
00:12:06,550 --> 00:12:07,650
when I've made something of myself,
I'll never forget you.

283
00:12:07,650 --> 00:12:08,720
You're like a real brother to me!

284
00:12:08,720 --> 00:12:10,170
When I get back, we'll swear brotherhood,

285
00:12:10,170 --> 00:12:10,700
brother.

286
00:12:10,840 --> 00:12:12,480
Okay, I won't keep you any longer.

287
00:12:12,480 --> 00:12:13,280
Get some rest.

288
00:12:20,410 --> 00:12:23,300
Yes, yes.

289
00:12:25,910 --> 00:12:27,120
Ura!

290
00:12:28,250 --> 00:12:29,050
Come on, Duan.

291
00:12:31,170 --> 00:12:32,430
Promise me something.

292
00:12:32,840 --> 00:12:34,320
No matter what happens in the future,

293
00:12:34,320 --> 00:12:36,720
don't tell him
that this money came from me.

294
00:12:37,480 --> 00:12:37,840
Okay.

295
00:12:38,250 --> 00:12:39,460
You've already said so.

296
00:12:39,460 --> 00:12:40,070
Relax.

297
00:12:40,100 --> 00:12:41,100
I won't say a word.

298
00:12:42,620 --> 00:12:43,480
But...

299
00:12:44,510 --> 00:12:45,840
I'm genuinely puzzled.

300
00:12:46,720 --> 00:12:47,300
Mr. Chu,

301
00:12:47,410 --> 00:12:49,410
you're not even that close.

302
00:12:50,630 --> 00:12:51,690
Why did you do that?

303
00:12:57,120 --> 00:12:57,780
Just right.

304
00:12:58,560 --> 00:12:59,620
Numbers check out.

305
00:13:03,100 --> 00:13:05,070
Here! Count it!

306
00:13:05,860 --> 00:13:07,740
No need. I trust you.

307
00:13:08,670 --> 00:13:10,130
He's quite a stand-up guy.

308
00:13:13,080 --> 00:13:16,550
Yellow cowhide, $10 a piece.

309
00:13:16,860 --> 00:13:18,670
Water buffalo hide, $6.

310
00:13:18,870 --> 00:13:19,820
No, no.

311
00:13:19,910 --> 00:13:21,030
These aren't the prices
we talked about last time.

312
00:13:21,030 --> 00:13:22,460
Why have the prices gone up so many times?

313
00:13:22,460 --> 00:13:24,060
That's how the market works.

314
00:13:24,100 --> 00:13:25,360
If you don't accept it,

315
00:13:25,500 --> 00:13:28,230
that deposit you just gave me
is non-refundable.

316
00:13:28,690 --> 00:13:29,690
What does he mean?

317
00:13:29,950 --> 00:13:31,970
H-He can do business like this?

318
00:13:32,220 --> 00:13:33,600
Are you kidding us?

319
00:13:33,820 --> 00:13:35,200
Look, i-if you do this,

320
00:13:35,240 --> 00:13:36,650
I'll call the police.

321
00:13:36,710 --> 00:13:38,640
We agreed right here the other day.

322
00:13:38,750 --> 00:13:39,960
Uh... the top-grade leather,

323
00:13:39,960 --> 00:13:41,070
$2.50 a piece,

324
00:13:41,100 --> 00:13:42,200
and this kind, $2 a piece.

325
00:13:42,200 --> 00:13:42,910
We did the math

326
00:13:42,910 --> 00:13:44,120
and brought exactly the money.

327
00:13:44,120 --> 00:13:45,450
You can go to the police.

328
00:13:46,050 --> 00:13:47,910
That's just how the market works.

329
00:13:48,150 --> 00:13:49,550
There's nothing I can do.

330
00:13:49,600 --> 00:13:52,510
Bring the rest at 5 PM tomorrow.

331
00:14:03,010 --> 00:14:04,870
You're jacking up the price on us!

332
00:14:06,240 --> 00:14:06,790
Ivan,

333
00:14:06,820 --> 00:14:08,480
do you think we're pushovers?

334
00:14:11,690 --> 00:14:12,710
I'm telling you,

335
00:14:13,280 --> 00:14:15,410
you're not bullying just the two of us.

336
00:14:15,670 --> 00:14:16,200
I'll tell

337
00:14:16,230 --> 00:14:17,370
every single Chinese merchant

338
00:14:17,370 --> 00:14:18,670
to stop doing business with you.

339
00:14:18,670 --> 00:14:19,740
Give us our money back right now.

340
00:14:19,740 --> 00:14:20,270
We're not buying.

341
00:14:20,270 --> 00:14:21,330
Do you understand?

342
00:14:27,630 --> 00:14:29,630
You think a few sticks will scare us?

343
00:14:30,460 --> 00:14:31,460
Kill me then.

344
00:14:31,670 --> 00:14:32,480
-Jun.
-Kill me, come on!

345
00:14:32,480 --> 00:14:33,520
Come on, kill me!

346
00:14:35,010 --> 00:14:36,210
Tomorrow won't work.

347
00:14:36,540 --> 00:14:38,600
We can't get that much money overnight.

348
00:14:38,600 --> 00:14:39,830
Give us two more days.

349
00:14:41,820 --> 00:14:43,480
The day after tomorrow, then.

350
00:14:45,940 --> 00:14:46,930
Wait, where...

351
00:14:47,960 --> 00:14:49,630
Where are we even supposed to
get the money?

352
00:14:49,630 --> 00:14:51,360
Who introduced this guy to you?

353
00:14:52,820 --> 00:14:54,380
That old bastard is truly rotten.

354
00:14:54,380 --> 00:14:55,520
Isn't he just swindling us?

355
00:14:55,520 --> 00:14:57,580
Complaining about it now won't help.

356
00:14:57,600 --> 00:14:59,020
We urgently need this batch of goods.

357
00:14:59,020 --> 00:15:00,900
The factory's all set to start work.

358
00:15:00,900 --> 00:15:02,080
But we don't have enough money.

359
00:15:02,080 --> 00:15:04,010
We put together exactly enough money
based on the original prices.

360
00:15:04,010 --> 00:15:04,890
How much are we short?

361
00:15:04,890 --> 00:15:05,620
Over 20,000.

362
00:15:06,320 --> 00:15:07,870
Even if we raise that amount,
it's useless.

363
00:15:07,870 --> 00:15:08,380
Look.

364
00:15:10,100 --> 00:15:11,470
There goes the profit margin.

365
00:15:11,470 --> 00:15:12,070
The profit

366
00:15:12,080 --> 00:15:14,940
wouldn't even cover
our round-trip train tickets.

367
00:15:15,430 --> 00:15:16,340
He knows for sure

368
00:15:16,340 --> 00:15:18,030
we can't do without his batch.

369
00:15:18,510 --> 00:15:19,120
Ivan

370
00:15:19,150 --> 00:15:20,970
has done this before.

371
00:15:21,750 --> 00:15:22,640
Years ago,

372
00:15:22,670 --> 00:15:24,390
he took over several small businesses.

373
00:15:24,390 --> 00:15:25,480
Now he has the largest supply of hide

374
00:15:25,480 --> 00:15:26,750
in the whole market.

375
00:15:27,200 --> 00:15:28,270
Relying on this,

376
00:15:28,290 --> 00:15:30,690
he often jacks up prices
whenever he wants.

377
00:15:30,720 --> 00:15:32,620
This guy has connections,

378
00:15:32,790 --> 00:15:35,540
so nobody dares to cross him.

379
00:15:35,980 --> 00:15:38,410
His crew often smuggles contraband

380
00:15:38,430 --> 00:15:40,100
in their shipments.

381
00:15:40,620 --> 00:15:42,950
They've made a lot of money
over the years.

382
00:15:43,010 --> 00:15:44,210
Just last month,

383
00:15:44,240 --> 00:15:45,840
they made a large sum of money

384
00:15:46,340 --> 00:15:48,340
through my friend's freight depot.

385
00:16:16,030 --> 00:16:17,830
You didn't come with sincerity.

386
00:16:19,280 --> 00:16:21,340
Didn't we already give you the money?

387
00:16:22,040 --> 00:16:23,060
Yellow cowhide,

388
00:16:23,290 --> 00:16:25,100
$2.50 a piece,

389
00:16:25,370 --> 00:16:27,970
and buffalo hide, $2 a piece.

390
00:16:28,130 --> 00:16:28,890
Am I right?

391
00:16:35,150 --> 00:16:38,220
I said $10 and $6.

392
00:16:44,310 --> 00:16:46,620
You have a shipment heading to Shenyang.

393
00:16:47,580 --> 00:16:49,180
Here's the tracking number.

394
00:16:53,030 --> 00:16:55,150
What's in that batch of goods—

395
00:16:56,290 --> 00:16:57,690
will it pass inspection?

396
00:16:58,390 --> 00:16:59,070
My friend

397
00:16:59,960 --> 00:17:00,670
is at

398
00:17:00,670 --> 00:17:02,170
Russian customs right now.

399
00:17:02,170 --> 00:17:03,710
If I can't leave today,

400
00:17:03,960 --> 00:17:05,060
your shipment

401
00:17:05,380 --> 00:17:07,640
will receive some "special attention."

402
00:17:16,810 --> 00:17:18,310
You dare investigate me?

403
00:17:18,710 --> 00:17:19,530
No, no, no.

404
00:17:21,220 --> 00:17:22,950
I'm not the one investigating!

405
00:17:23,109 --> 00:17:24,890
Russian customs will be!

406
00:17:25,640 --> 00:17:28,380
If you honor the original prices,

407
00:17:28,980 --> 00:17:31,050
we'll put this whole thing behind us.

408
00:17:31,750 --> 00:17:33,240
Otherwise, we can just wait here

409
00:17:33,240 --> 00:17:34,420
and see who comes looking for you first—

410
00:17:34,420 --> 00:17:36,310
buyers

411
00:17:36,500 --> 00:17:38,160
or Russian customs officers.

412
00:17:47,460 --> 00:17:48,270
Frankly,

413
00:17:49,440 --> 00:17:51,170
we wouldn't be bold enough

414
00:17:51,280 --> 00:17:52,030
to do business out here

415
00:17:52,030 --> 00:17:53,890
without our connections in Russia.

416
00:17:53,890 --> 00:17:56,420
I'll come pick up the goods
tomorrow morning.

417
00:18:03,070 --> 00:18:04,820
Step aside. Let him go.

418
00:18:10,490 --> 00:18:11,690
Spasibo (thank you).

419
00:18:26,160 --> 00:18:27,220
Harasho! Harasho!

420
00:18:27,220 --> 00:18:28,040
Lower, lower, lower!

421
00:18:28,040 --> 00:18:28,920
Lower, lower!

422
00:18:29,610 --> 00:18:30,220
Lower it! Keep going!

423
00:18:30,220 --> 00:18:31,640
Over here! Come on, come on!

424
00:18:31,640 --> 00:18:32,220
Hold it steady.

425
00:18:32,220 --> 00:18:33,390
A bit more out, a bit more out!

426
00:18:33,390 --> 00:18:35,520
Good. Harasho! Lower it down!

427
00:18:46,720 --> 00:18:47,570
Careful.

428
00:18:47,740 --> 00:18:48,540
Wait a moment.

429
00:18:50,380 --> 00:18:52,190
Let's have a meal together.

430
00:18:53,570 --> 00:18:54,700
We'll skip the meal.

431
00:18:54,740 --> 00:18:57,000
We can just stick to business from now on.

432
00:19:13,750 --> 00:19:14,570
This time,

433
00:19:15,000 --> 00:19:16,000
we're definitely going to make big money.

434
00:19:15,050 --> 00:19:19,750
[Braised Noodles]

435
00:19:16,780 --> 00:19:17,330
Well, just come back

436
00:19:17,330 --> 00:19:18,030
and work with us.

437
00:19:18,030 --> 00:19:19,560
I was too hard on you before.

438
00:19:20,740 --> 00:19:22,710
I made myself clear that day too.

439
00:19:23,240 --> 00:19:23,850
There are

440
00:19:23,880 --> 00:19:25,310
two things in life that make me happiest.

441
00:19:25,310 --> 00:19:26,550
One is playing the saxophone.

442
00:19:26,550 --> 00:19:27,700
The other is...

443
00:19:28,610 --> 00:19:30,220
seeing my buddies

444
00:19:30,250 --> 00:19:31,450
doing better than me.

445
00:19:31,530 --> 00:19:32,790
I hope the two of you succeed!

446
00:19:32,790 --> 00:19:34,000
Alright then.

447
00:19:34,140 --> 00:19:35,400
Invest in us.

448
00:19:35,440 --> 00:19:36,660
When we make money, we'll split it.

449
00:19:36,660 --> 00:19:38,500
Doesn't that mean
I, your buddy, am doing well?

450
00:19:38,500 --> 00:19:39,440
I'm fine with a dividend share,

451
00:19:39,440 --> 00:19:40,520
but I can't invest—

452
00:19:40,550 --> 00:19:41,550
I've got no money.

453
00:19:41,920 --> 00:19:42,250
Then,

454
00:19:42,290 --> 00:19:43,010
just go borrow a bit from your mom.

455
00:19:43,010 --> 00:19:43,610
That's it.

456
00:19:43,770 --> 00:19:45,760
[Braised Noodles]

457
00:19:43,900 --> 00:19:45,400
Now you think of my mom.

458
00:19:45,550 --> 00:19:46,510
During the New Year,

459
00:19:46,510 --> 00:19:48,430
you rarely visited her!

460
00:19:48,460 --> 00:19:49,380
And we live so close.

461
00:19:49,380 --> 00:19:50,220
I was busy.

462
00:19:50,240 --> 00:19:50,920
During the New Year,

463
00:19:50,920 --> 00:19:51,940
I was in Russia, wasn't I?

464
00:19:51,940 --> 00:19:52,920
What should we do then?

465
00:19:52,920 --> 00:19:54,220
Besides, your mom is my mom.

466
00:19:54,220 --> 00:19:54,700
How about this?

467
00:19:54,700 --> 00:19:55,550
Okay, thank you.

468
00:19:55,550 --> 00:19:56,770
Let Mom invest.

469
00:19:56,980 --> 00:19:58,610
When we make money, we give Mom her share.

470
00:19:58,610 --> 00:20:00,010
Give Mom... Give Mom a...

471
00:20:00,510 --> 00:20:01,140
Xiaojun!

472
00:20:01,550 --> 00:20:02,080
Xiaojun!

473
00:20:03,410 --> 00:20:04,130
Mr. Duan!

474
00:20:06,240 --> 00:20:07,160
What a coincidence!

475
00:20:07,160 --> 00:20:08,180
What a coincidence!

476
00:20:08,180 --> 00:20:08,900
Where are you sitting?

477
00:20:08,900 --> 00:20:10,920
-How come I didn't see you earlier?
-I was in the private room.

478
00:20:10,920 --> 00:20:12,160
You're here to eat too?

479
00:20:12,160 --> 00:20:13,660
My buddy likes this place.

480
00:20:13,700 --> 00:20:15,010
No wonder I didn't see you earlier.

481
00:20:15,010 --> 00:20:16,680
Come on! Join us and have a drink!

482
00:20:16,680 --> 00:20:18,310
-I've already eaten.
-Sit! Let's eat together!

483
00:20:18,310 --> 00:20:18,900
I just finished.

484
00:20:18,900 --> 00:20:20,430
Well, let me introduce you.

485
00:20:20,750 --> 00:20:22,030
This is Shengli. Liangliang.

486
00:20:22,030 --> 00:20:23,570
-We're buddies doing business together.
-Nice to meet you.

487
00:20:23,570 --> 00:20:24,240
Nice to meet you, sir.

488
00:20:24,240 --> 00:20:25,170
This is Mr. Duan.

489
00:20:25,220 --> 00:20:26,310
Mr. Duan lent us the money

490
00:20:26,310 --> 00:20:27,310
for our business.

491
00:20:28,010 --> 00:20:29,420
Thank you, Mr. Duan!

492
00:20:29,500 --> 00:20:30,570
-Thank you!
-Mr. Duan!

493
00:20:30,570 --> 00:20:32,420
You really helped us in our hour of need!

494
00:20:32,420 --> 00:20:33,050
Never mind that.

495
00:20:33,050 --> 00:20:33,920
None of that formality.

496
00:20:33,920 --> 00:20:35,450
How's your business going?

497
00:20:35,570 --> 00:20:36,160
Well,

498
00:20:36,180 --> 00:20:37,090
we just finished stocking up the goods,

499
00:20:37,090 --> 00:20:38,090
and the three of us

500
00:20:38,160 --> 00:20:39,220
are having a little celebration here.

501
00:20:39,220 --> 00:20:39,850
Yes, yes.

502
00:20:40,010 --> 00:20:40,640
Mr. Duan, I'll say it straight—

503
00:20:40,640 --> 00:20:41,310
without you,

504
00:20:41,310 --> 00:20:42,440
we couldn't have started this business.

505
00:20:42,440 --> 00:20:43,270
Let me toast you!

506
00:20:43,270 --> 00:20:44,400
Come on, the three of us toast you!

507
00:20:44,400 --> 00:20:44,800
To you!

508
00:20:45,010 --> 00:20:45,790
-Use this cup!
-I'll pass on the alcohol.

509
00:20:45,790 --> 00:20:46,980
-Use this cup!
-I've already had quite a bit.

510
00:20:46,980 --> 00:20:48,260
Then I'll down one for you!

511
00:20:48,260 --> 00:20:48,640
No...

512
00:20:51,750 --> 00:20:52,410
Xiaojun!

513
00:20:52,500 --> 00:20:53,840
That's enough.

514
00:20:54,240 --> 00:20:55,100
Once your business is
properly up and running,

515
00:20:55,100 --> 00:20:56,010
we'll celebrate properly then.

516
00:20:56,010 --> 00:20:57,680
Okay, okay.

517
00:20:57,750 --> 00:20:58,880
Actually, Xiaojun,

518
00:20:58,880 --> 00:21:00,610
let me tell you the truth today.

519
00:21:00,720 --> 00:21:02,540
That money didn't come from me.

520
00:21:02,660 --> 00:21:04,000
It came from a good friend of mine.

521
00:21:04,000 --> 00:21:04,750
He specifically asked me

522
00:21:04,750 --> 00:21:05,950
to give you the money.

523
00:21:06,230 --> 00:21:07,170
We were actually having dinner together

524
00:21:07,170 --> 00:21:07,700
in a private room today.

525
00:21:07,700 --> 00:21:08,400
He just stepped out.

526
00:21:08,400 --> 00:21:09,260
By the way, Xiaojun,

527
00:21:09,260 --> 00:21:09,850
let me take you out

528
00:21:09,850 --> 00:21:10,770
to meet that friend.

529
00:21:10,770 --> 00:21:11,440
He's a really great guy.

530
00:21:11,440 --> 00:21:12,790
-Alright, alright, sure!
-Let's go.

531
00:21:12,790 --> 00:21:13,660
More friends, more opportunities, right?

532
00:21:13,660 --> 00:21:14,460
I'll go say hello first.

533
00:21:14,460 --> 00:21:15,340
Go ahead!

534
00:21:15,670 --> 00:21:16,840
Take care, Mr. Duan!

535
00:21:17,380 --> 00:21:18,240
Which one is he?

536
00:21:18,440 --> 00:21:19,460
You'll definitely need his help someday.

537
00:21:19,460 --> 00:21:20,510
Where did this Mr. Duan come from?

538
00:21:20,510 --> 00:21:21,900
He looks a bit unfamiliar.

539
00:21:21,900 --> 00:21:22,510
I don't know him either.

540
00:21:22,510 --> 00:21:23,290
I have no idea.

541
00:21:23,290 --> 00:21:24,720
He gave money to people
he's never even met?

542
00:21:24,720 --> 00:21:26,480
That's really something.

543
00:21:26,920 --> 00:21:28,250
That guy's car is something.

544
00:21:28,250 --> 00:21:29,450
What kind of car is it?

545
00:21:33,960 --> 00:21:35,220
Hello, sir. Thank you.

546
00:21:35,380 --> 00:21:36,240
Thank you, sir.

547
00:21:39,710 --> 00:21:41,830
[Seasons Change Hostel]

548
00:21:44,110 --> 00:21:45,480
[Seasons Change Hostel]

549
00:21:53,960 --> 00:21:54,680
Don't drink too much.

550
00:21:54,680 --> 00:21:55,290
-I'm heading off.
-Okay, okay.

551
00:21:55,290 --> 00:21:55,940
Okay, let's have a drink later.

552
00:21:55,940 --> 00:21:57,000
Alright, alright.

553
00:21:57,050 --> 00:21:57,750
Okay, okay.

554
00:21:57,880 --> 00:21:58,230
Bye.

555
00:21:58,440 --> 00:21:59,150
Bye.

556
00:22:02,140 --> 00:22:03,070
Come on, cheers.

557
00:22:05,030 --> 00:22:07,110
You should just invest the money.

558
00:22:07,180 --> 00:22:07,790
You don't have to do anything.

559
00:22:07,790 --> 00:22:08,660
Just sit back and wait for your share.

560
00:22:08,660 --> 00:22:09,290
I always thought

561
00:22:09,290 --> 00:22:10,570
it was Mr. Duan who lent us the money.

562
00:22:10,570 --> 00:22:11,670
It turns out to be that guy outside.

563
00:22:11,670 --> 00:22:13,470
That guy outside has real class.

564
00:22:13,700 --> 00:22:14,430
That guy said

565
00:22:14,540 --> 00:22:15,430
we don't even

566
00:22:15,720 --> 00:22:16,640
have to pay interest on this money.

567
00:22:16,640 --> 00:22:18,470
Wow, and he looks sharp too.

568
00:22:18,490 --> 00:22:19,550
Really decent guy.

569
00:22:20,490 --> 00:22:21,650
That guy is the real deal.

570
00:22:21,650 --> 00:22:22,270
Yeah.

571
00:22:23,320 --> 00:22:26,010
Ma Xiaojun. Come with me for a sec.

572
00:22:27,580 --> 00:22:28,140
What's going on?

573
00:22:28,140 --> 00:22:30,230
A few drinks and you call my full name?

574
00:22:31,590 --> 00:22:32,570
What's wrong,

575
00:22:33,570 --> 00:22:34,370
Young Master?

576
00:22:35,690 --> 00:22:37,040
They drove off and left!

577
00:22:38,290 --> 00:22:38,970
What?

578
00:22:39,340 --> 00:22:40,940
Never seen a nice car before?

579
00:22:41,090 --> 00:22:41,770
I'll borrow it someday

580
00:22:41,770 --> 00:22:43,130
and let you drive it.

581
00:22:43,270 --> 00:22:44,930
You jerk, Ma Xiaojun!

582
00:22:46,500 --> 00:22:47,720
Ma Xiaojun, have you no conscience?

583
00:22:47,720 --> 00:22:48,240
Do you know

584
00:22:48,240 --> 00:22:49,590
that was Chu Caiyuan's money?

585
00:22:49,590 --> 00:22:50,750
What Chu Caiyuan?

586
00:22:50,810 --> 00:22:52,280
You've had a few drinks
and lost your mind?

587
00:22:52,280 --> 00:22:53,930
How was I supposed to know
whose money it was?

588
00:22:53,930 --> 00:22:55,080
Are you crazy?

589
00:22:55,750 --> 00:22:57,160
Are you crazy?

590
00:22:58,140 --> 00:22:59,380
Let go of me!

591
00:22:59,830 --> 00:23:00,430
Screw you!

592
00:23:05,060 --> 00:23:05,860
Are you crazy?

593
00:23:06,060 --> 00:23:07,120
Are you crazy?

594
00:23:07,770 --> 00:23:08,900
You're insane!

595
00:23:09,660 --> 00:23:10,870
You drank too much!

596
00:23:10,940 --> 00:23:11,550
Jun!

597
00:23:15,840 --> 00:23:17,410
Ungrateful thing.

598
00:23:17,770 --> 00:23:18,850
You're not my friend anymore.

599
00:23:18,850 --> 00:23:19,670
Liangliang.

600
00:23:19,830 --> 00:23:20,900
Don't touch me!

601
00:23:23,220 --> 00:23:24,280
Don't be like this.

602
00:23:25,820 --> 00:23:27,080
You drank too much!

603
00:23:29,180 --> 00:23:30,580
You two do your business.

604
00:23:30,610 --> 00:23:32,330
You two go ahead
and do your business together!

605
00:23:32,330 --> 00:23:33,860
If you dare walk away today,

606
00:23:34,400 --> 00:23:36,110
we're done for good!

607
00:23:38,440 --> 00:23:39,370
Then we are done.

608
00:23:41,390 --> 00:23:43,050
I don't care if you drop dead out there!

609
00:23:43,050 --> 00:23:43,780
Liangliang!

610
00:23:49,710 --> 00:23:51,020
I really want to curse!

611
00:23:51,050 --> 00:23:51,980
Why didn't you

612
00:23:51,980 --> 00:23:53,500
tell me about this earlier?

613
00:23:53,500 --> 00:23:54,110
How was I supposed to know

614
00:23:54,110 --> 00:23:55,540
you borrowed the money from him?

615
00:23:55,540 --> 00:23:56,050
I've lived

616
00:23:56,050 --> 00:23:57,240
my whole life,

617
00:23:57,350 --> 00:23:58,270
and I've never once

618
00:23:58,270 --> 00:23:59,240
betrayed my buddy!

619
00:23:59,240 --> 00:24:00,420
What must Liangliang

620
00:24:00,420 --> 00:24:01,790
be thinking of me right now?

621
00:24:01,790 --> 00:24:02,850
Hurry up. Hurry...

622
00:24:03,550 --> 00:24:04,530
Wait, we spent all the money on the hides.

623
00:24:04,530 --> 00:24:05,260
Look at this.

624
00:24:09,330 --> 00:24:10,160
The first batch of goods

625
00:24:10,160 --> 00:24:11,090
is almost ready.

626
00:24:11,290 --> 00:24:12,700
We have to sell it quickly.

627
00:24:12,700 --> 00:24:13,330
Let's sell it quickly

628
00:24:13,330 --> 00:24:14,590
and pay the money back.

629
00:24:44,240 --> 00:24:45,170
Is it a good time?

630
00:24:45,860 --> 00:24:47,120
I'd like to talk to you.

631
00:24:47,530 --> 00:24:48,740
Let's go for a walk?

632
00:24:49,920 --> 00:24:50,960
Let's talk inside.

633
00:24:50,960 --> 00:24:52,160
I don't want to go out.

634
00:25:28,600 --> 00:25:29,130
Ranran,

635
00:25:30,700 --> 00:25:31,850
we've been acting awkward with each other

636
00:25:31,850 --> 00:25:32,950
for so long.

637
00:25:34,940 --> 00:25:36,380
Can you tell me what's wrong?

638
00:25:36,380 --> 00:25:38,180
I really can't stand it anymore.

639
00:25:40,380 --> 00:25:42,440
What have you been thinking about us?

640
00:25:43,030 --> 00:25:44,110
And if I did something wrong,

641
00:25:44,110 --> 00:25:44,980
just tell me.

642
00:25:45,010 --> 00:25:45,990
I can change.

643
00:25:47,310 --> 00:25:48,570
I really don't know...

644
00:25:49,720 --> 00:25:50,680
what happened between us.

645
00:25:50,680 --> 00:25:51,700
It's driving me crazy.

646
00:25:51,700 --> 00:25:52,960
Every day I lie in bed,

647
00:25:52,980 --> 00:25:54,270
I-I don't dare to close my eyes.

648
00:25:54,270 --> 00:25:55,140
As soon as I close them,

649
00:25:55,140 --> 00:25:55,850
I see you when you first came to

650
00:25:55,850 --> 00:25:57,280
the hostel.

651
00:25:58,200 --> 00:25:59,110
My mind is full of

652
00:25:59,110 --> 00:25:59,980
images of us.

653
00:26:02,680 --> 00:26:03,810
I want to sort it out.

654
00:26:04,880 --> 00:26:06,540
I know I can't.

655
00:26:10,530 --> 00:26:11,440
But I want to tell you

656
00:26:11,440 --> 00:26:12,770
that I haven't changed.

657
00:26:15,940 --> 00:26:18,000
My feelings for you haven't changed.

658
00:26:25,070 --> 00:26:26,000
I've changed.

659
00:26:27,310 --> 00:26:28,910
You haven't changed either.

660
00:26:29,000 --> 00:26:29,660
I have.

661
00:26:30,830 --> 00:26:31,560
You haven't.

662
00:26:31,850 --> 00:26:33,050
That's not an excuse.

663
00:26:36,580 --> 00:26:37,440
Liangliang...

664
00:26:42,330 --> 00:26:43,860
Let's just leave it at this.

665
00:26:45,940 --> 00:26:46,670
Let's end it.

666
00:26:53,640 --> 00:26:54,180
Why?

667
00:26:59,240 --> 00:27:00,710
There's no why.

668
00:27:06,460 --> 00:27:08,090
I did love you.

669
00:27:09,880 --> 00:27:12,140
A reckless, all-consuming kind of love.

670
00:27:14,460 --> 00:27:15,240
But you also know,

671
00:27:15,240 --> 00:27:16,500
when I came to Beijing,

672
00:27:17,510 --> 00:27:20,020
what I wanted to do most
was to be an actress.

673
00:27:20,690 --> 00:27:22,460
That's my biggest dream.

674
00:27:24,070 --> 00:27:25,800
I know you want to be an actress.

675
00:27:27,450 --> 00:27:28,980
And I never once thought about

676
00:27:28,980 --> 00:27:30,010
stopping you from being an actress

677
00:27:30,010 --> 00:27:30,830
or acting.

678
00:27:30,850 --> 00:27:32,500
I've always supported you.

679
00:27:34,070 --> 00:27:35,270
But the reality is

680
00:27:35,270 --> 00:27:36,600
that these two things

681
00:27:37,400 --> 00:27:38,680
have conflicted.

682
00:27:40,980 --> 00:27:43,250
These are two clearly

683
00:27:43,290 --> 00:27:44,780
separate paths.

684
00:27:49,480 --> 00:27:50,720
When both paths

685
00:27:50,740 --> 00:27:52,510
were laid in front of me...

686
00:27:55,310 --> 00:27:56,400
I made a choice.

687
00:28:00,830 --> 00:28:01,560
I thought...

688
00:28:03,570 --> 00:28:05,370
as long as you felt the same as me,

689
00:28:06,770 --> 00:28:09,200
I'd go down the same path with you
to the end.

690
00:28:14,020 --> 00:28:15,820
But you actually told me that...

691
00:28:18,380 --> 00:28:20,520
you weren't ready.

692
00:28:20,610 --> 00:28:21,550
It's not that I didn't want to

693
00:28:21,550 --> 00:28:22,660
or that I was afraid.

694
00:28:22,660 --> 00:28:24,190
I was just caught off guard.

695
00:28:24,500 --> 00:28:25,850
I never imagined

696
00:28:25,940 --> 00:28:27,340
my first time would be...

697
00:28:27,500 --> 00:28:28,350
like that.

698
00:28:28,370 --> 00:28:29,950
I never imagined this.

699
00:28:30,720 --> 00:28:31,640
I know.

700
00:28:32,680 --> 00:28:34,010
It wasn't your fault.

701
00:28:37,500 --> 00:28:39,360
But that was my first time as well.

702
00:28:45,440 --> 00:28:47,680
It's too late to talk about it now.

703
00:28:49,570 --> 00:28:50,850
You must have

704
00:28:50,880 --> 00:28:51,540
some idea of

705
00:28:51,570 --> 00:28:53,630
what happened between Mr. Chu and me.

706
00:28:54,610 --> 00:28:55,850
I don't want to keep going over this

707
00:28:55,850 --> 00:28:57,190
again and again.

708
00:28:58,290 --> 00:28:59,160
Don't force me

709
00:28:59,200 --> 00:29:01,160
to reopen my old wound again and again,

710
00:29:01,160 --> 00:29:01,680
okay?

711
00:29:03,960 --> 00:29:04,570
Ranran.

712
00:29:10,850 --> 00:29:12,240
It's all in the past.

713
00:29:12,830 --> 00:29:13,830
It's all over now.

714
00:29:14,440 --> 00:29:15,500
I can't get over it.

715
00:29:19,700 --> 00:29:21,560
I know I can't explain it clearly.

716
00:29:23,130 --> 00:29:25,460
But I've thought it through very clearly.

717
00:29:25,640 --> 00:29:27,050
I know what I want.

718
00:29:30,810 --> 00:29:32,010
I want to...

719
00:29:34,110 --> 00:29:36,640
I want to be with you—

720
00:29:37,010 --> 00:29:38,830
really be with you for a lifetime.

721
00:29:38,830 --> 00:29:39,740
I'll try my best

722
00:29:39,880 --> 00:29:41,680
to give you everything you want,

723
00:29:41,680 --> 00:29:42,640
everything you dream of.

724
00:29:42,640 --> 00:29:43,640
I'm pregnant.

725
00:29:58,590 --> 00:29:59,440
Just go.

726
00:30:06,940 --> 00:30:08,160
Whenever I see you,

727
00:30:09,900 --> 00:30:10,760
I can't help...

728
00:30:11,140 --> 00:30:13,220
I can't help thinking...

729
00:30:16,210 --> 00:30:18,310
if I had chosen

730
00:30:18,350 --> 00:30:19,920
another path back then...

731
00:30:23,640 --> 00:30:26,660
what would we be like now?

732
00:33:02,330 --> 00:33:02,830
Ranran!

733
00:33:04,290 --> 00:33:04,770
Ranran.

734
00:33:07,440 --> 00:33:08,570
Where are you going?

735
00:33:09,770 --> 00:33:10,600
I don't know.

736
00:33:11,810 --> 00:33:12,530
I was afraid

737
00:33:12,530 --> 00:33:14,170
you'd just up and leave without a word.

738
00:33:14,170 --> 00:33:15,900
You always say I'm like a child.

739
00:33:16,400 --> 00:33:18,130
Aren't you being childish too?

740
00:33:33,710 --> 00:33:34,970
Let's have a good talk.

741
00:33:37,830 --> 00:33:38,560
Liangliang.

742
00:33:41,480 --> 00:33:42,610
I have to leave here.

743
00:33:43,700 --> 00:33:44,570
If I stay,

744
00:33:46,640 --> 00:33:48,840
we'll only make each other suffer more.

745
00:33:50,380 --> 00:33:51,700
I can't face you.

746
00:33:53,570 --> 00:33:54,700
Don't push me, okay?

747
00:33:57,740 --> 00:33:59,600
The things you're telling me now—

748
00:34:00,830 --> 00:34:03,160
maybe I wouldn't have understood before.

749
00:34:04,250 --> 00:34:05,720
But now, I do.

750
00:34:07,050 --> 00:34:08,820
If none of this had happened,

751
00:34:09,340 --> 00:34:10,920
whatever vows I made to you,

752
00:34:11,840 --> 00:34:13,570
whatever feelings I declared—

753
00:34:14,880 --> 00:34:17,080
maybe it was all just heat of the moment.

754
00:34:17,760 --> 00:34:18,460
But I know

755
00:34:18,460 --> 00:34:20,790
that every word
I'm saying to you right now

756
00:34:20,840 --> 00:34:23,239
is something I've thought through deeply.

757
00:34:24,900 --> 00:34:27,159
I already missed my chance with you once.

758
00:34:27,230 --> 00:34:27,920
I don't want to

759
00:34:27,920 --> 00:34:29,150
miss it again.

760
00:34:32,190 --> 00:34:33,280
I don't want...

761
00:34:35,010 --> 00:34:36,380
our future...

762
00:34:40,030 --> 00:34:41,500
to be clouded by the past.

763
00:34:43,300 --> 00:34:44,080
You said

764
00:34:45,500 --> 00:34:47,070
you didn't know where to go

765
00:34:47,730 --> 00:34:48,760
or what your future life

766
00:34:48,760 --> 00:34:49,830
would be like.

767
00:34:51,530 --> 00:34:53,389
That's something I can't accept.

768
00:34:54,170 --> 00:34:55,650
If you leave now...

769
00:34:58,450 --> 00:34:59,670
and wander the world,

770
00:35:01,800 --> 00:35:03,380
I'll go find you right away.

771
00:35:04,420 --> 00:35:06,620
I'll search the ends of the earth for you

772
00:35:06,860 --> 00:35:08,350
until I find you.

773
00:35:08,530 --> 00:35:10,670
Then, I'll say everything
I'm telling you now,

774
00:35:10,670 --> 00:35:12,230
all over again.

775
00:35:14,650 --> 00:35:15,820
Instead of wasting time

776
00:35:15,820 --> 00:35:16,800
on that,

777
00:35:19,210 --> 00:35:21,180
why don't we use that time

778
00:35:22,760 --> 00:35:23,820
to love each other?

779
00:35:28,210 --> 00:35:29,070
Shen Ranran...

780
00:35:35,860 --> 00:35:36,330
I...

781
00:35:37,690 --> 00:35:39,090
I know I don't have much money now

782
00:35:39,090 --> 00:35:40,380
to buy you a ring.

783
00:35:41,780 --> 00:35:43,910
But the money I made going to Russia...

784
00:35:45,320 --> 00:35:46,170
with them—

785
00:35:49,760 --> 00:35:50,530
I used all of it

786
00:35:50,530 --> 00:35:52,260
to buy this little gift for you.

787
00:35:52,420 --> 00:35:53,170
I just never

788
00:35:53,170 --> 00:35:54,840
found the right moment.

789
00:36:00,210 --> 00:36:01,010
Just consider

790
00:36:01,940 --> 00:36:03,320
that I owe you a ring.

791
00:36:04,280 --> 00:36:06,410
I'll definitely buy one for you later.

792
00:36:06,460 --> 00:36:08,190
But today, I want to tell you...

793
00:36:10,420 --> 00:36:11,610
you can't leave me.

794
00:36:15,440 --> 00:36:17,400
My world—Tao Liangliang's world—

795
00:36:19,280 --> 00:36:20,810
means nothing without you.

796
00:36:25,090 --> 00:36:26,710
I'll definitely buy you...

797
00:36:27,230 --> 00:36:28,830
a ring you like in the future.

798
00:36:42,880 --> 00:36:43,740
Shen Ranran...

799
00:36:49,000 --> 00:36:50,930
I can accept everything about you.

800
00:36:55,630 --> 00:36:57,050
Will you be with me?

801
00:37:32,460 --> 00:37:34,500
I'll go back to Beijing
to check in with Director Weng.

802
00:37:34,500 --> 00:37:37,160
You go keep a close eye on
the factory in Wenzhou.

803
00:37:37,260 --> 00:37:38,860
You've found yourself such a

804
00:37:38,860 --> 00:37:39,880
good business setup.

805
00:37:39,880 --> 00:37:41,190
Zhuang Zhuang and your father-in-law

806
00:37:41,190 --> 00:37:42,280
are at the factory every day,
watching over things.

807
00:37:42,280 --> 00:37:42,670
They wish they could

808
00:37:42,670 --> 00:37:43,570
check every single stitch.

809
00:37:43,570 --> 00:37:44,170
Sometimes your father-in-law

810
00:37:44,170 --> 00:37:45,320
even does it himself.

811
00:37:45,320 --> 00:37:46,400
I was thinking
I could help you keep an eye on

812
00:37:46,400 --> 00:37:47,660
things here in Russia,

813
00:37:47,760 --> 00:37:48,530
and you could go back

814
00:37:48,530 --> 00:37:51,010
and spend more time
with your father-in-law.

815
00:37:51,010 --> 00:37:52,470
Let's talk about it later.

816
00:37:53,260 --> 00:37:55,260
With such a large volume of orders
right now,

817
00:37:55,260 --> 00:37:57,090
our product quality and production

818
00:37:57,090 --> 00:37:57,850
must keep up.

819
00:37:58,150 --> 00:37:59,010
Otherwise, all the effort

820
00:37:59,010 --> 00:37:59,780
Sophia spent opening the market for us

821
00:37:59,780 --> 00:38:00,710
would be wasted.

822
00:38:00,980 --> 00:38:01,670
My friends,

823
00:38:01,670 --> 00:38:02,700
let me tell you—

824
00:38:02,920 --> 00:38:03,730
these leather shoes

825
00:38:03,730 --> 00:38:05,880
have been incredibly popular here!

826
00:38:05,940 --> 00:38:07,760
I've compiled the sales figures.

827
00:38:07,760 --> 00:38:08,560
Take a look.

828
00:38:09,510 --> 00:38:10,730
Especially this one

829
00:38:10,820 --> 00:38:11,730
and this one.

830
00:38:11,840 --> 00:38:13,670
They've been selling particularly well!

831
00:38:13,670 --> 00:38:14,660
Is it possible

832
00:38:14,820 --> 00:38:16,050
that it's you who's popular?

833
00:38:16,050 --> 00:38:17,150
You're the reason

834
00:38:17,150 --> 00:38:17,980
we have

835
00:38:18,010 --> 00:38:19,210
a market here.

836
00:38:20,360 --> 00:38:20,870
No.

837
00:38:21,400 --> 00:38:23,800
They sell well
because of the good quality.

838
00:38:24,320 --> 00:38:24,770
Right.

839
00:38:24,920 --> 00:38:26,260
To tell you the truth,

840
00:38:26,320 --> 00:38:28,850
some shoes from Chinese factories

841
00:38:29,300 --> 00:38:30,760
were of very poor quality.

842
00:38:31,070 --> 00:38:33,470
They felt like
they were made of cardboard.

843
00:38:33,690 --> 00:38:35,090
They couldn't last a week

844
00:38:35,150 --> 00:38:37,030
and would fall apart once they got wet.

845
00:38:37,030 --> 00:38:37,900
Things like that

846
00:38:37,900 --> 00:38:40,230
damaged the reputation of Chinese goods.

847
00:38:40,530 --> 00:38:42,260
But our products are different.

848
00:38:42,260 --> 00:38:42,960
The quality is good,

849
00:38:42,960 --> 00:38:44,600
so everyone snaps them up.

850
00:38:45,420 --> 00:38:46,150
Sometimes I feel like

851
00:38:46,150 --> 00:38:47,750
I'm taking advantage of you.

852
00:38:48,070 --> 00:38:49,230
I haven't really contributed much

853
00:38:49,230 --> 00:38:50,460
to your business.

854
00:38:51,690 --> 00:38:53,970
What do you mean, "your business"?

855
00:38:54,070 --> 00:38:56,830
This is our business, right?

856
00:38:56,880 --> 00:38:57,820
Even though Xu and Zhuang Zhuang

857
00:38:57,820 --> 00:38:59,510
started it as a husband-and-wife shop,

858
00:38:59,510 --> 00:39:00,320
once the business grows,

859
00:39:00,320 --> 00:39:00,940
we could

860
00:39:00,940 --> 00:39:02,780
open an international division in Russia.

861
00:39:02,780 --> 00:39:03,510
Sounds good!

862
00:39:04,420 --> 00:39:05,420
Sounds good to me.

863
00:39:05,800 --> 00:39:07,730
See? An international division.

864
00:39:07,900 --> 00:39:09,150
An international division.

865
00:39:09,150 --> 00:39:11,630
[Guest Room]

866
00:39:15,280 --> 00:39:16,080
Can I help you?

867
00:39:18,020 --> 00:39:18,760
Could you tell me

868
00:39:18,760 --> 00:39:20,000
which room Shen Ranran is in?

869
00:39:20,000 --> 00:39:20,730
Who are you?

870
00:39:22,380 --> 00:39:23,260
I'm her friend.

871
00:39:23,650 --> 00:39:24,260
Wait.

872
00:39:24,500 --> 00:39:25,800
Does Ranran know you're coming?

873
00:39:25,800 --> 00:39:27,740
[Parking Area]

874
00:39:27,050 --> 00:39:27,710
Excuse me,

875
00:39:27,810 --> 00:39:28,860
I'll ask you one last time—

876
00:39:28,860 --> 00:39:30,090
which room is Shen Ranran staying in?

877
00:39:30,090 --> 00:39:30,960
Can you tell me or not?

878
00:39:30,960 --> 00:39:31,510
Well,

879
00:39:31,820 --> 00:39:33,340
j-just tell me

880
00:39:33,360 --> 00:39:34,110
what you want with her.

881
00:39:34,110 --> 00:39:34,600
None of your business.

882
00:39:34,600 --> 00:39:35,680
What do you mean, "none of my business"?

883
00:39:35,380 --> 00:39:38,540
[Parking Area]

884
00:39:35,710 --> 00:39:36,710
I'm the owner here.

885
00:39:36,710 --> 00:39:37,170
It is my business.

886
00:39:37,170 --> 00:39:37,960
Why are you getting physical?

887
00:39:37,960 --> 00:39:38,780
-None of your business.
-No!

888
00:39:38,780 --> 00:39:39,380
Wait!

889
00:39:39,530 --> 00:39:41,260
-What are you doing?
-Shen Ranran!

890
00:39:41,260 --> 00:39:42,190
What do you want?

891
00:39:42,320 --> 00:39:42,800
Let go of me!

892
00:39:42,800 --> 00:39:43,780
Shen Ranran!

893
00:39:43,840 --> 00:39:44,960
Why are you here?

894
00:39:47,240 --> 00:39:48,070
You again.

895
00:39:48,940 --> 00:39:49,820
I'm telling you—

896
00:39:49,820 --> 00:39:51,160
I must see Ranran today.

897
00:39:51,230 --> 00:39:51,760
No way.

898
00:39:52,500 --> 00:39:53,150
Get out of my way.

899
00:39:53,150 --> 00:39:53,760
No way.

900
00:39:54,920 --> 00:39:55,500
Listen up,

901
00:39:55,500 --> 00:39:56,760
I've had enough of you!

902
00:39:56,920 --> 00:39:58,020
Don't push it!

903
00:39:58,050 --> 00:39:59,380
Or I won't go easy on you!

904
00:39:59,400 --> 00:39:59,830
Step aside!

905
00:39:59,830 --> 00:40:01,150
You still can't go in!

906
00:40:01,280 --> 00:40:01,800
What?

907
00:40:02,650 --> 00:40:03,530
Asking for a beating, huh?

908
00:40:02,770 --> 00:40:07,380
[Guest Room]

909
00:40:03,760 --> 00:40:04,760
Stop right there!

910
00:40:05,000 --> 00:40:05,420
What are you doing?

911
00:40:05,420 --> 00:40:05,960
Let go!

912
00:40:06,480 --> 00:40:07,190
Let go of us!

913
00:40:07,460 --> 00:40:08,390
Help!

914
00:40:08,480 --> 00:40:09,780
They're hitting people!

915
00:40:09,780 --> 00:40:10,840
Haven't had enough beating?

916
00:40:10,840 --> 00:40:12,130
Haven't had enough?

917
00:40:15,860 --> 00:40:16,590
Let go of him!

918
00:40:16,800 --> 00:40:17,660
Let go of him!

919
00:40:18,420 --> 00:40:19,090
Bastard!

920
00:40:19,610 --> 00:40:21,030
Who told you to touch her?

921
00:40:21,230 --> 00:40:21,730
Boss!

922
00:40:22,380 --> 00:40:22,940
Ranran!

923
00:40:23,760 --> 00:40:24,530
What do you want?

924
00:40:24,530 --> 00:40:25,260
Let go of him!

925
00:40:25,380 --> 00:40:26,000
Let go!

926
00:40:30,110 --> 00:40:31,510
All of you, get back here!

927
00:40:43,960 --> 00:40:44,460
Ranran.

928
00:40:46,320 --> 00:40:47,050
Come with me.

929
00:40:48,030 --> 00:40:49,490
Let's find a place to talk.

930
00:40:51,650 --> 00:40:53,090
I'm not going with you.

931
00:40:54,610 --> 00:40:55,610
I quit acting.

932
00:40:56,500 --> 00:40:58,160
I have nothing to do with you!

933
00:40:58,590 --> 00:41:00,050
Even if you quit acting...

934
00:41:02,260 --> 00:41:03,660
we can still be together.

935
00:41:05,340 --> 00:41:06,540
I'm getting married.

936
00:41:09,320 --> 00:41:10,140
Back off!

937
00:41:16,710 --> 00:41:17,730
Are you sure

938
00:41:18,090 --> 00:41:19,590
the person you're marrying

939
00:41:19,590 --> 00:41:20,920
loves you more than I do?

940
00:41:27,210 --> 00:41:27,820
I am sure.

941
00:41:28,690 --> 00:41:29,230
Ranran.

942
00:41:30,340 --> 00:41:31,270
I was young once.

943
00:41:31,760 --> 00:41:32,230
I know

944
00:41:32,250 --> 00:41:34,250
"the world for two" that you imagine

945
00:41:34,940 --> 00:41:36,170
is not necessarily real.

946
00:41:36,170 --> 00:41:37,380
This world is big.

947
00:41:38,300 --> 00:41:40,260
This hostel is my world.

948
00:41:41,460 --> 00:41:42,630
Please leave.

949
00:41:48,070 --> 00:41:49,000
If my love for you

950
00:41:49,860 --> 00:41:50,500
has become

951
00:41:50,500 --> 00:41:51,700
a kind of harassment,

952
00:41:52,920 --> 00:41:53,570
I promise

953
00:41:54,730 --> 00:41:55,460
I will leave.

954
00:41:58,480 --> 00:42:00,050
But when you're out there alone,

955
00:42:00,050 --> 00:42:01,250
don't get bullied...

956
00:42:03,380 --> 00:42:04,440
and don't get hurt.

957
00:42:06,820 --> 00:42:08,280
If you ever really need me,

958
00:42:09,070 --> 00:42:09,920
give me a call.

959
00:42:13,630 --> 00:42:14,160
Goodbye.

960
00:42:16,280 --> 00:42:16,800
Sorry.

961
00:42:16,860 --> 00:42:17,300
Leave!

962
00:42:43,670 --> 00:42:44,800
-Ranran, you're bleeding!
-Are you alright?

963
00:42:44,800 --> 00:42:45,390
Ranran!

964
00:42:45,840 --> 00:42:46,500
What's wrong? What's wrong?

965
00:42:46,500 --> 00:42:48,860
Are you alright? Kid!

966
00:42:49,500 --> 00:42:51,090
Go call an ambulance!

967
00:42:52,130 --> 00:42:53,110
Kid!

968
00:42:53,230 --> 00:42:54,490
Are you alright, Ranran?
